# Solid Skills — 3DAIGC-API

Project skill: `.agents/skills/solid/` ([ramziddin/solid-skills](https://github.com/ramziddin/solid-skills)). Lock: `skills-lock.json`.

## When to apply

Use on **new adapters**, **router/service refactors**, **scheduler changes**, and **code review** — not on log triage, model prefetch, or env/server ops.

## Stack overrides (skill is TypeScript/NestJS-biased)

| Layer | Apply as |
|-------|----------|
| API | FastAPI routers thin; business logic in `core/` and `adapters/` |
| Jobs | Scheduler + Redis queue; adapters implement model interface |
| Config | `config/models.yaml` + adapter class; verify `/api/v1/system/models` |

## Project rules win over skill defaults

1. **Minimize scope** — smallest correct diff; no drive-by refactors.
2. **Tests** — add when requested or for regressions; TDD for new pure helpers/adapters, not every config tweak.
3. **Legacy** — do not split large adapters for line-count targets unless refactor is the task.
4. **Complementary changes** — API shape changes need matching OpenNexus3DStudio client updates.

## Prefer from the skill

Single responsibility per adapter, interface segregation for model params, code smells in touched files, clean architecture at module boundaries.
